            <!-- 3. BINARY: DEFINE & WHY -->
            <section>
                <h3>What Is Binary?</h3>
                <div class="key-term fragment">
                    <h3>Binary</h3>
                    <p>Base-2 system using only 0 and 1, matching digital electronics (OFF/ON).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cols">
                    <div class="box fragment">
                        <strong>Why It Exists</strong>
                        <ul class="small-text">
                            <li>Voltage low/high → 0/1, reliable for hardware</li>
                            <li>Noise-tolerant; simple switching</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="box-blue fragment">
                        <strong>Clarify</strong>
                        <p class="small-text">Is binary chosen because it is <em>easy for humans</em> or because it is <em>robust for circuits</em>?</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- 4. BINARY: HOW IT WORKS & DECODING -->
            <section>
                <h3>How Do Bits Make Numbers?</h3>
