                    </div>
                </section>
            </section>

            <!-- 6. Clarification Question (Binary) -->
            <section>
                <h3>Clarify: Binary Understanding</h3>
                <div class="question-box">Why does adding more bits increase the maximum value?</div>
                <div class="fragment box-blue">
                    <p><strong>Because</strong> each new bit doubles the available range (next power of 2 place value).</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- 7. HEX: DEFINE & WHY -->
            <section>
                <h3>What Is Hexadecimal?</h3>
                <div class="key-term fragment">
                    <h3>Hexadecimal</h3>
                    <p>Base-16 system using digits 0–9 and A–F (10–15) to represent values compactly.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cols">
                    <div class="box fragment">
                        <strong>Why It Exists</strong>
                        <ul class="small-text">
                            <li>Human-friendly shorthand for long binary strings</li>
                            <li>Maps neatly to 4-bit nibbles (1 hex digit = 4 bits)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="box-blue fragment">
                        <strong>Question</strong>
                        <p class="small-text">Where do we see hex in real products?</p>
                        <p class="small-text fragment">Examples: error codes (0x8007…), MAC addresses, colour codes (#3FA7D6).</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

