            <section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Binary Addition (8-bit)</h2>
                    <p class="small-text">Add two positive 8-bit integers; watch the carry.</p>
                    <div class="box-blue">
                        <p><strong>Example:</strong> 01010101 + 00111001</p>
                        <p class="small-text fragment">1+1 = 0 (carry 1); propagate carries across</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="fragment box">
                        <p><strong>Result:</strong> 10000110 (no overflow because we kept 8 bits?)</p>
                        <p class="small-text">Carry into bit 9? then overflow.</p>
                    </div>
                    <p class="small-text" style="margin-top:1rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-down blue"></i> Overflow check</p>
                </section>

                <section data-background="#f4f6f8">
                    <h3>Overflow</h3>
                    <div class="box">
                        <p><strong>Example:</strong> 11110000 + 11110000</p>
                        <p class="fragment"><strong>Work:</strong> result bits = <code>11100000</code> with a carry out of the 8th bit</p>
                        <p class="fragment"><strong>Meaning:</strong> Sum needs 9 bits → <span class="gold">overflow</span> (too big for 8-bit register)</p>
                    </div>
                </section>
